{{Coord|43|44|4.74|N|7|25|16.8|E|scale:1563_type:landmark_region:MC|display=title}} {{Infobox Grand Prix race report |Type = F1 |Country = Monaco |Grand Prix = Monaco |Date = 29 May |Year = 1960 |Image = Circuit de Monaco 1950.png |Caption = |Official name = XVIII [[Monaco Grand Prix|Grand Prix Automobile de Monaco]] |Location = [[Circuit de Monaco]], [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]] |Course = Street Circuit |Course_mi = 1.954 |Course_km = 3.145 |Distance_laps = 100 |Distance_mi = 195.400 |Distance_km = 314.500 |Pole_Driver = [[Stirling Moss]] |Pole_Team = [[Team Lotus|Lotus]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]] |Pole_Time = 1:36.3 |Pole_Country = United Kingdom |Fast_Driver = [[Bruce McLaren]] |Fast_Team = [[Cooper Car Company|Cooper]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]] |Fast_Time = 1:36.2 |Fast_Lap = |Fast_Country = New Zealand |First_Driver = [[Stirling Moss]] |First_Team = [[Team Lotus|Lotus]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]] |First_Country = UK |Second_Driver = [[Bruce McLaren]] |Second_Team = [[Cooper Car Company|Cooper]]-[[Coventry Climax|Climax]] |Second_Country= New Zealand |Third_Driver = [[Phil Hill]] |Third_Team = [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]] |Third_Country = USA }} The '''1960 Monaco Grand Prix''' was a [[Formula One]] [[motor race]] held at [[Circuit de Monaco|Monaco]] on 29 May 1960. It was race 2 of 10 in the [[1960 World Championship of Drivers]] and race 2 of 9 in the [[1960 International Cup for Formula One Manufacturers]].
The race was won by [[Stirling Moss]] in a [[Lotus 18]] entered by the [[Rob Walker Racing Team|R.R.C Walker Racing Team]]. It was the first World Championship F1 victory for the marque.
