{{Infobox company| name = Cumerio Med| logo = | type = [[public company|private]] | foundation = 1932 | location = [[Pirdop]], [[Bulgaria]]| key_people = | num_employees = 1,420<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cumerio.com/en/ourCompany/groupStructure/operations/pirdop/ |title=Pirdop Cumerio Med |publisher= |accessdate=2007-01-03 }}</ref> (2007) | revenue = [[Image:Green Arrow Up.svg|12px]] US$2.3 billion (2007) | industry = [[copper]] | }}
'''Cumerio Med''' was [[Bulgaria]]'s largest [[copper|copper smelting company]] producing around 240,000 tonnes of [[copper|smelted copper]] and around 60,000 tonnes of [[copper|copper cathodes]] each year. In 1997, the company was sold to '''Cumerio''' a company from [[Belgium]] for US$80 million<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.easibulgaria.org/Privatization_KRassen.doc |title=Политическа икономия на раздържавяването в България |publisher= |accessdate=2007-03-16 }}</ref> but in 2007, the company was bought by [[Germany|German]] company [[Norddeutsche Affinerie]].
