{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = El Comercio | logo = File:El Comercio.svg | image = | caption = | type = Daily newspaper | format = [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|Tabloid]] | owners = [[Grupo Vocento]] | founder = | publisher = | editor = Marcelino Gutiérrez | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{start date and age|df=y|1878|9|2}} | political = | language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] | ceased publication = | headquarters = [[Gijón]], [[Asturias]] | circulation = 24,056 | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = {{URL|http://www.elcomercio.es/}} }} '''''El Comercio''''' is a [[daily newspaper]] in [[Spain]]. Published in [[Gijón]], it is the second-largest newspaper by circulation in [[Asturias]], with a daily circulation of 24,000.<ref name="OJD Diarios">{{cite web|url=http://www.ojd.es/OJD/Portal/diarios_ojd/_4DOSpuiQo1Y_FOivPcLIIA |title=Diarios |work=Oficina de Justificación de la Difusión |accessdate=25 May 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110429094834/http://www.ojd.es/OJD/Portal/diarios_ojd/_4DOSpuiQo1Y_FOivPcLIIA |archivedate=29 April 2011 |df=dmy }}</ref>
==History and profile== ''El Comercio'' was first published on 2 September 1878.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Media Markets and Newspapers|journal=SFN Flash|date=7 January 2004|volume=7|issue=1|url=http://www.wan-press.org/IMG/pdf/04Q_03_SFN_Flash_FullText-2.pdf|accessdate=17 February 2015}}</ref> Since 1995 the paper has been part of [[Grupo Vocento]]. In 1996 it acquired ''[[La Voz de Avilés]]'', and it continues that name for its [[Avilés]] edition.
In 2006 ''El Comercio'' had a circulation of 27,843 copies.<ref>{{cite book|author=José María Magone|title=Contemporary Spanish Politics|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vbh5UkfRtbAC&pg=PA266|accessdate=21 February 2015|year=2009|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-415-42188-1|page=266}}</ref>
