{{more footnotes|date=December 2016}} {{infobox organization | name = European Science Fiction Society | image = David Lally.jpg | alt = | caption = Dave Lally, (former) chairman of the European Science Fiction Society, during the general meeting at [[Eurocon]] in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]], 2011. | logo = | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | abbreviation = ESFS | motto = | formation = {{start date and age|1972|paren=yes}} | founder = | founding_location = [[Trieste]], [[Italy]] | type = [[Science fiction]] organisation | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = Promote [[science fiction]] | headquarters = | location = Europe{{clarify|date=December 2016|reason=where in Europe?}} | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | affiliations = [[Eurocon]] | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = {{URL|esfs.info}} }} The '''European Science Fiction Society''' is an international organisation of professionals and fans who are committed to promoting [[science fiction]] in [[Europe]] and European science fiction worldwide.
The organisation was founded at the first [[Eurocon]] (European Science Fiction Convention), which was held in 1972 in [[Trieste]], [[Italy]]. Since that time, the organisation has organized Eurocons at least every two years. The organisation also administrates the [[European SF Awards]].
The society's officers (as re-elected in 2013 in [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]]) are:<ref>[http://www.esfs.info//]. European Science Fiction Society.</ref> *Chairman: Carolina Gómez Lagerlöf, ([[Sweden]]) *Secretary: Gareth Kavanagh ([[Ireland]]) *Treasurer: Vanja Kranjcevic ([[Croatia]]) *Vice Chairman: Saija Kyllönen ([[Finland]]) *Award Administrator: Bridget Wilkinson ([[United Kingdom]])
Bridget Wilkinson served as a society officer for 25 years before standing down at the 2016 [[Eurocon]], held in [[Barcelona]], [[Spain]]. Before that, she ran Fans Across The World co-ordinating science fiction fans from the former [[Eastern Europe]] with their counterparts in the West.
