'''The Diocese of Farafangana''' is a [[Roman Catholic]] [[Diocese]] under the [[Archdiocese of Fianarantsoa]] in [[Madagascar]]. It is based in the town of [[Farafangana]] and was erected on 8 April 1957. It performs the [[Latin Rite|Latin]] or [[Rite]]. The Diocese covers approximately {{convert|20,390|km|mi|abbr=on}}. As of 2004, the diocese population was about 900,000, with 7.9% Catholic. 36 priests were in the Diocese for a ratio of 1,985 Catholics for every 1 Priest. There are no bishop of the Diocese since  [[Benjamin Marc Ramaroson]] has become archibishop of Roman catholic archdiocese of Antsiranana.

